accessibility.text: Hyperbolic geometry: non-Euclidean geometry, studies spaces of constant negative curvature
Various models, here we focus on the Poincaré disk
Hyperbolic geometry: non-Euclidean geometry, studies spaces of constant negative curvature
Various models, here we focus on the Poincaré disk
volume grows exponentially with radius (like in trees!)
geodesics are circles perpendicular to boundary
can embed trees with arbitrary low distortions in      (!= Euclidean space) [Gromov 1987, De Sa 2018]
